snippet.textDisplay: People here posting all kinds of hate comments I have just one thing to say. You people are behaving like hypocrites. To be honest I hadn't heard of this song until it came on Coke Studio. It may be a famous song in Orissa but I don't think many around India might have been aware of it until this video. Now if a woman has come out and brought this on a national platform you people instead of appreciating her efforts are making derogatory comments. So what if she danced on the song! I mean learn to have some broad mindsets. Don't you think instead of taking offence you should use this song as a stepping stone towards bringing forth the culture and folklore of Orissa. People appealing in the SC against the artists should record the original song again (in better quality, please the video quality of the song is awful) and make people understand the lyrics of the song. If these so called self righteous people have ownership of this song then why haven't they done anything to make this a prominent song? And as far as copyright infringement is concerned I heard this song is played at weddings and sung very widely around Orissa so do they ask permission from the singers of this song before playing it at their weddings? Guess not!!! Such hypocrites. Seeking publicity from  artists who have actually brought forward something so beautiful for us Indians to enjoy...

snippet.textDisplay:
In my village many people sings. They includes balad charauu, chhel charauu, kirtan wala, dand nachu, nachhnia etc. they sings well. whether they have correct scale? or correct wording?? no one bothers. even no one bothers to their body language.

The Female singer here is actually doing more Odishi dance then actually singing the song. Forget about her pronunciation of the words- she pounces lai jauchhe (it should have nai jauchhe), she pounces "manne" which means (meaning)" actually should have mane (in heart). She pounces Dihi (body), actually should have bihi (God), she pounces Khanji (arrange) or khandi (i do not  know but may be pieces) , she pounces Tuhu tuhu ( No idea what it means) actually should have been kuhu kuhu. Not rani 'tale' suta 'male' it should have been rani take suta bandhi.

Actually, since it was sang earlier thats why there is controversy. One may not expect silly mistakes from establish singers includes all those present at that stage.

Otherwise every odd has its own style.
the song might be getting play in MARS even in more different ways. Who know. And people might be liking that as well.

snippet.textDisplay:
Orissa is a very traditional place with its own dress up, own culture, own language, own belief, own talents, etc. Many are not aware about it because Indian media is busy capturing only the informations about the most developed cities of India. If our countries main stream cinema "Bollywood" starts promoting orissa traditions, music, etc. in this way then its a great thing to achieve in near future. Thanks to MTV & thanks to Sona Mahapatra & Rituraj Mohanty, the prides of Orissa and now of India. 

The song is a milestone for Orissa folk music. Nicely sang by the original singer before & now the new version by Sona Mahapatra & Rituraj Mohanty.. Great going guys... Love you all..
